item.dc:creator: @tyyy9 tyyy9
item.description:
@tyyy9 wrote:

[quote=“The Wanderer, post:16, topic:407213”][quote author=ambientX link=topic=508500.msg3689107#msg3689107 date=1312007589]
Don’t use someone’s source that isn’t PI or delta. I would recommend you download the server and client included in this tutorial I made. It is newb friendly.

moparisthebest.com

moparisthebest.com

programming, irc, cars


[/quote]
Because max players online being around 100 and having memory leaks is a good thing right? The only good thing in PI is content, and the quality of that content is very poor.

I beg to differ I just started up Hyperion and it looks great so far but I will check your server

Now the next thing you are going to need to understand is the http://rswiki.gyrat.in/index.php?title=317_Protocol

Remember, everything you see is the client, everything you do is the server. The server is simply just using what the client has. You develop everything around the client. I would read from Player Updating, since Hyperion has login finished. If you have any question feel free to post here. :)[/quote] Thanks the Wanderer that will help a lot I also just got a hold of a PI server so im gonna go try it now, if it doesnt work ill go back to hyperion
